{%- comment -%}
  Pickup availability — section wrapper for the BOPIS (Buy-Online-
  Pick-up-In-Store) snippet so it can be re-rendered via Shopify's
  Section Rendering API on variant change.

  Theme Store testing checklist (Section 7 — Local pickup) requires
  the pickup banner to update *dynamically* when the customer picks a
  different variant: a variant available at five locations must show
  five locations, the same product's variant available only outside
  the pickup network must drop the banner entirely, and so on.
  Achieving this without a full page reload requires the section to
  be requestable as `/variants/{variant_id}?section_id=pickup-
  availability`; the route returns the product page rendered in the
  context of that variant, scoped by section_id to just this block,
  which `assets/product-form.js` swaps into the `[data-pickup-
  availability]` container on variant:change.

  The actual rendering logic lives in `snippets/pickup-availability`
  so it stays callable from any product context (PDP, quick-view,
  cart-drawer upsell) without duplicating the markup.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- render 'pickup-availability',
  variant: product.selected_or_first_available_variant,
  product: product
-%}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "t:sections.pickup-availability.name",
  "tag": "div",
  "class": "kt-pickup-section"
}
{% endschema %}
